onLineSrc.orName: The Enterprise Web Portal and GIS Office

dataIdInfo.idAbs: This dataset represents Washington Metropolitan Area Transit Authority (WMATA) rail centerlines (inbound and outbound tracks showing as single line). All WMATA GIS data is stored and exported in WMATA LDP NAD 1983 [NSRS2007] US Feet.

placeKeys.keyword: Arlington County, City of Alexandria, City of Fairfax, City of Falls Church, District of Columbia, Fairfax County, Loudoun County, Montgomery County, Prince George's County, Prince William County, Washington DC, Washington DC Metropolitan Area, WMATA Service Area

themeKeys.keyword: Transit, METRO, WMATA, Transit Operation, Planning, MetroAccess, Paratransit

Consts.useLimit: Data Are Restricted to Internal WMATA Personnel Only. These data should not be distributed to users unless distribution is explicitly granted. Please check sources, scale, accuracy, currentness and other available information. Please confirm that you are using the most recent copy of both data and metadata.

dataIdInfo.idPurp: The rail track centerline features serve as base information for use in GIS systems for general planning, analytical, and research purposes. Feed information to WMATA Website, and Metroview (ArcGIS Server Flex Web applications).
dataIdInfo.envirDesc: Microsoft Windows 7 Version 6.1 (Build 7601) Service Pack 1; Esri ArcGIS 10.2.2.3552

dataLineage.statement: Use CAD drawing (System Map_MD NAD83 Datum.dwg) from Surveyors Office as basis for rail system maps and network. The cad file were imported and converted to GIS layer.

dataSource.srcDesc: CAD drawing from Track, Structures and Facilities (TSFA). Precise alignment of all mainline track, station platforms, and yards, annotated with 100' chain marker stationings and rail station names. Does not include crossover and pocket track.

citRespParty.rpPosName: Assistant Chief Engineer, Track, Structures and Facilities (TSFA)
